    "previewFile": "25-07-26_iii---the-monster-is-the-harbinger-of-category-crises_012825_PREVIEW.jpg",
    "thumbnailFile": "25-07-26_iii---the-monster-is-the-harbinger-of-category-crises_012825_THUMB.jpg",
    "mainFile": "25-07-26_iii---the-monster-is-the-harbinger-of-category-crises_012825.png",
    "title": "iii---the-monster-is-the-harbinger-of-category-crises",
    "date": "25-07-26",
    "description": "I felt enraged by how many of them stood there, scowls on their faces, or pointing and jeering, and filming what I experienced as a beautiful march. I don’t know what’s in their hearts, but I think the pictures get across in their facial expressions and body language a mixture of disgust, humour, and maybe a bit of intrigue or longing?",
    "contenttype": "Photography"
  },
  {
    "originalFileName": "ii-alwaysescapes.png",
    "fileName": "25-07-26_ii---the-monster-always-escapes_012825",
    "originalDir": "/Users/dylanhemmings/Desktop/photographystaging",
    "originalPath": "/Users/dylanhemmings/Desktop/photographystaging/ii-alwaysescapes.png",
    "destinationDir": "/Users/dylanhemmings/05.Site/static/resources/images/art/photography",
    "previewFile": "25-07-26_ii---the-monster-always-escapes_012825_PREVIEW.jpg",
    "thumbnailFile": "25-07-26_ii---the-monster-always-escapes_012825_THUMB.jpg",
    "mainFile": "25-07-26_ii---the-monster-always-escapes_012825.png",
    "title": "ii---the-monster-always-escapes",
    "date": "25-07-26",
    "description": "I took my camera hoping to capture pictures of trans joy and improve my confidence in publicly transitioning (which I did get!). However, as we were marching, I felt more moved to try to capture the looks we got from spectators, random people out shopping or hanging out, obviously taken aback by the parade.",
    "contenttype": "Photography"
  },
  {
    "originalFileName": "vi-policestheboundaries.png",
    "fileName": "25-07-26_vi---the-monster-polices-the-boundaries-of-the-possible_012825",
    "originalDir": "/Users/dylanhemmings/Desktop/photographystaging",
    "originalPath": "/Users/dylanhemmings/Desktop/photographystaging/vi-policestheboundaries.png",
    "destinationDir": "/Users/dylanhemmings/05.Site/static/resources/images/art/photography",
    "previewFile": "25-07-26_vi---the-monster-polices-the-boundaries-of-the-possible_012825_PREVIEW.jpg",
    "thumbnailFile": "25-07-26_vi---the-monster-polices-the-boundaries-of-the-possible_012825_THUMB.jpg",
    "mainFile": "25-07-26_vi---the-monster-polices-the-boundaries-of-the-possible_012825.png",
    "title": "vi---the-monster-polices-the-boundaries-of-the-possible",
    "date": "25-07-26",
    "description": "I hope the series works partly to rub their faces in how ridiculous and hateful they appear, and to make the point that, just as cis society spectates trans people as a hyper-visible cultural scapegoat, we can spectate them right back.",
    "contenttype": "Photography"
  },
  {
