    "title": "iv---the-monster-dwells-at-the-gates-of-difference",
    "date": "25-07-26",
    "description": "Being early on in my transition, I find that my experience of being trans in public is mediated and policed by a hyper-vigilance of the expressions on strangers faces, the side eyes and half-laughter as you pass by. Trans pride was the only time I felt the safety in numbers enough to photograph these hostile gazes, without fear of aggression.",
    "contenttype": "Photography"
